A simple lexical analyser 

A lexical analyser converts a stream of characters into a stream of tokens. A token refers to a meaningful group of characters. Eg: int refers to a datatype, # refers to a preprocessor directive etc
Every program runs through a lexical analyser, the lexical analyser is a program that defines the tokens that a language accepts. i.e what are the valid 

A simple lexical analyser consists of 3 parts
1. Declaration
2. Rules
3. Auxillary functions

Part 1 : The Declaration







yywrap() just add this function prototype

yytext() stores the previously read token, can access this using yytext, strlen(yytext)

yyleng stores the length of the previosly read token

